Sugar Prices May Drop on Increased India Exports, Survey Says

-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m   a n d   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-06-23T23:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/sugar-prices-may-drop-on-increased-india-exports-survey-says.html
Sugar may fall next week as exports
increase in  India , the world’s second-largest producer.  Seven of nine traders, analysts and brokers surveyed by
Bloomberg News said raw sugar in New York may decrease. One said
it would gain, and one it would be little changed. Before today,
futures for October delivery gained 2.8 percent this week to
26.08 cents a pound on ICE Futures U.S.  Seven of nine respondents said refined sugar on  London ’s
NYSE Liffe will drop. One said it would gain, and one was
neutral. Futures for August delivery advanced 0.8 percent this
week through yesterday.  Four respondents said refined sugar’s premium over raw may
widen, three said it would narrow and two were neutral.  To contact the reporters on this story:
